<h2>Project brief</h2>

<p>Working in a group of five, we had to create a digital product and a poster of our product based on a student guide about a topic of our choosing. We decided to create an international student guide website about Manchester, helping international students find the best things to do within the city centre.</p>

<p>We decided as a group to use bright bold colours across the website to try and reflect what Manchester is all about. In terms of the logo, we decided to use a bee inside a love heart. The bee is the symbol of Manchester, indicating the city to be a hard working, energetic city.</p>

<p>For the typography, we decided to use a sans-serif font as we wanted to make it as easy as possible for the user to read, especially if the user had any visual disabilities.</p>

<p>We also had to create a large sized poster to advertise our product. On the poster are statistics from our user research, screenshots of the completed website and a description about the website.</p>

